we should use POLYMORPHISM again!
we just need a List on DataSource to store our target obj
(we have polymorphism here, a list to store SpreadSheet,Chart,...)

we need some functionality like
add/remove/iterate on this list
if we implement it on DataSource class, we violate "single responsibility concept"
so we need separate class for this
we put these logics on abstract class as "SUBJECT"
and extend our DataSource class to Subject class to inherit these functionalities

each observer should know how to update themselves
so they have update()
we notify() them from setter
and they update themselves!

Note: Observer pattern sometimes called "publish subscribe" pattern
      because subject class play the role of a publisher
      it publishes changes in its state,
      and observers are subscribers to those event


    <<abstract class>>                                    <<interface>>
+---------------------------+ <>------------------> +---------------------------+
|          Subject          |                       |         Observer          |
+---------------------------+                       +---------------------------+
| + attach(obs)             |                       | + update()               |
| + detach(obs)             |                       +---------------------------+
| + notify()                |                                   ^
+---------------------------+                                   |
            ^                                                   |
            |                                                   |
+---------------------------+                       +---------------------------+
|      ConcreteSubject      |                       |     ConcreteObserver      |       Note:  by Observer Interface
+---------------------------+                       +---------------------------+              we can make respect on "open close concept"
| like our DataSource class |                       | like SpreadSheet/Chart    |              if we have new ConcreteObserver to extend our app
+---------------------------+                       +---------------------------+              we don't need any modification on old classes
                                                                                               we just create one new ConcreteObserver



COMMUNICATION STYLE

push style
when we are using update()
we can pass the new value to update

pull style
we can put a field to store the reference of the ConcreteSubject (DataSource obj)
on our ConcreteObserver (SpreadSheet/Chart )
when we use update, just pull what we need from base DataSource obj

Note: we can use single int primitive like here
      or entire obj like dataSource obj to communicate
      if we use push style, later if we add, remove fields
      we probably need to modify what we pass to update()
      (sometimes each observer need different values)
      so pull style is more flexible!

Note: using pull style means we add coupling to system
      (we add some dependency to our observers class)
      it's not bad type of coupling!
      we never have zero coupling!

Note: direction of coupling is important
      if we have these dependency on DataSource (like fields based on Char,SpreadSheet)
      it was so bad!
      if we want to add new observer, we need to modify DataSource too!



